text: A triacontadigon or icosidodecagon is a shape with 32 sides and 32 corners. == Regular triacontadigon == All sides of a regular triacontadigon are the same length. Each corner is 168°. All corners added together equal 5400°. === Area === The amount of space a regular triacontadigon takes up is :\text{Area} = 8a^2 \left(1+ \sqrt{2} + \sqrt{4 +2 \sqrt{2} } +\sqrt{8 +4 \sqrt{2} +2 \sqrt{20 +14 \sqrt{2} } }\right). a is the length of one of its sides. 32
title: Triacontadigon
